statements.documentation:
progress from epoch A to B
end of epoch A:
- store epoch A external assets
- increment epoch
start of epoch B:
- use epoch A end external assets for totalAssets()
- deposit/redeem accordingly
- add/subtract external assets with delta
- get delta asset
- get total external assets
- collect deposits
- calculate shares to redeem
- * positive delta (more deposits):
- deposit delta for more shares
- transfer out delta to farmer
- store remaining for withdrawal
- * negative delta (more redeems):
- transfer in delta assets from farmer
- redeem (burn) shares
- store epoch B totalSupply and totalAsset
- store epoch B starting external assets
